\begin{verbatim}
frf_reconstruction(res, poles, freq; lr, ur, type)
\end{verbatim}
Reconstruct a frequency response function (FRF) from its residues and poles.

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{res::Array\{Complex, 3\}}: Residues corresponding to each pole


\item \texttt{poles::Vector\{Complex\}}: Poles extracted from the FRF


\item \texttt{freq}: Frequency vector


\item \texttt{lr::Matrix\{Complex, 2\}}: Lower residuals (default: zeros)


\item \texttt{ur::Matrix\{Complex, 2\}}: Upper residuals (default: zeros)


\item \texttt{type::Symbol}: Type of FRF to reconstruct

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{:dis}: displacement (default)


\item \texttt{:vel}: velocity


\item \texttt{:acc}: acceleration

\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{H\_rec::Array\{Complex, 3\}}: Reconstructed FRF

\end{itemize}

\begin{verbatim}
compute_residuals(prob, res, poles)
\end{verbatim}
Compute lower and upper residuals of a frequency response function (FRF) given its residues and poles.

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{prob::EMAProblem}: Structure containing FRF data and frequency vector


\item \texttt{res::Array\{Complex, 3\}}: Residues corresponding to each pole


\item \texttt{poles::Vector\{Complex\}}: Poles extracted from the FRF

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Outputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{lr::Matrix\{Complex, 2\}}: Lower residuals


\item \texttt{ur::Matrix\{Complex, 2\}}: Upper residuals

\end{itemize}
\begin{verbatim}
compute_residuals(prob, res, poles)
\end{verbatim}
Compute lower and upper residuals of a half-spectrum given its residues and poles.

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{prob::OMAProblem}: Structure containing half-spectrum data and frequency vector


\item \texttt{res::Array\{Complex, 3\}}: Residues corresponding to each pole


\item \texttt{poles::Vector\{T\}}: Poles extracted from the half-spectrum

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Outputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{lr::Matrix\{Complex, 2\}}: Lower residuals


\item \texttt{ur::Matrix\{Complex, 2\}}: Upper residuals

\end{itemize}

\begin{verbatim}
mode2residues(ms, poles, idx_m, idx_e)
\end{verbatim}
Compute the mode residues from mode shapes and poles.

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{ms::Matrix\{Complex, 2\}}: Mode shapes matrix


\item \texttt{poles::Vector\{Complex\}}: Poles extracted from the FRF


\item \texttt{idx\_m::Vector\{Int\}}: Indices of measurement locations


\item \texttt{idx\_e::Vector\{Int\}}: Indices of excitation locations

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{res::Array\{Complex, 3\}}: Residues corresponding to each pole


\item \texttt{ci::Vector\{Complex\}}: Scaling constants for each mode

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Note} The mode shapes are supposed to be real and mass-normalized.
